headline: BEN Q3 Deep Dive: Alternatives, Tech, and Platform Shifts Shape Outlook Amid Negative Market Reaction
summary: Global investment management firm Franklin Resources (NYSE:BEN) reported revenue ahead of Wall Streets expectations in Q3 CY2025, with sales up 36.5% year on year to $2.34 billion. Its non-GAAP profit of $0.67 per share was 14% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
